result.execSummary:
All charges against Raven D Wehrmann in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Raven D Wehrmann is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Review hearing on October 31, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
Warrant for Commitment, signed by CC Herring on 10/04/2022.

2:13 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marrufo. Defendant Raven D Wehrmann in court, in custody. Attorney Steven Hughes in court for Raven D Wehrmann. 

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading. 
State of Texas is requesting extradition for Arson Intend Damage Habitat/Place of Worship, a F1 Felony.
Court Conducts Waiver of Extradition Colloquy with the defendant.
Defendant waives their right to extradition.
Court accepts the waiver of extradition.
Parties and the court sign the waiver of extradition and Court Commissioner signs the Order for Commitment.

The State gives its bail recommendation.
Defense gives its bail recommendation.

BOND:
THE COURT REMANDS THE DEFENDANT TO THE CUSTODY OF THE WAUKESHA COUNTY JAIL.

State of Texas is to be notified ASAP that the defendant is available for pick up.
Court sets matter for a review hearing to ensure the defendant was picked up.
Review hearing scheduled for October 31, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
